latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Less on products, high on trends : that was my Go-To Mantra for this look. 
No liner, No Kajal, No highlighter, No contour.. have used only minimal products for this makeup look.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Cut-Crease Eye-Makeup Tutorial
#MakeupBrushChallenge
Make your Eyeshadow POP!!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ever faced this problem when you apply an eyeshadow, and it doesn’t pop or highlight as it should.. Well, Try using this amazing hack to make your eyeshadow POP. 
Even if you have applied a concealer as the base starting with your eye makeup, the color may not look as bright as you want it to be. Try using a white pencil before you apply your eyeshadow or pigment. (The simple trick behind this is the color seems the most bright when we use a white canvas).
And see the magic. 😍😍

latestIgtvVideos.title: Convert your daily makeup into a party one!!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There are times when we get back home from work, and suddenly friends make plans for a party. 
But we don’t feel like washing the face and starting with the makeup all over again. 
This video will help you to quickly convert your daily look into a party one- without starting your makeup all over again! 
Doing a smokey eye over here.
1. Apply a thick eyeliner- preferably a gel one- so that you can smudge it. Using @clinique Gel eyeliner.
2. Smudge it with a blending brush and bake it with black eyeshadow.
3. Using a brown eyeshadow as a transition color. And with a bigger blending brush - Blend! 
4. Apply some color on your lower lash line too. 
5. Clean the excess dust with Makeup remover, and shape with a Q-tip if necessary.
6. Avoiding the foundation here- cos there’s already some on the face left. Just using the concealer to highlight my under eyes, and T zone. Using @maccosmetics Studio finish concealer in shade NC30.
7. Applying some blusher and mascara 
8. Add some glitter to the eyes with the help of two way gel. Using @maccosmetics glitter and @paccosmetic two way gel.
9. Wear lashes and change your clothes and you’re ready to roll.

latestIgtvVideos.title: My Go-to Look!!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Okay, so I am gonna start by saying that I have been camera conscious all through my life,and this has only been possible because of the love that you all have showered upon me. 
I have tried recording my everyday Go-to look!! I am writing all the steps that I followed for you’ll to understand better:
1. Used @maccosmetics prep+prime fix+ as the first step to skin prep. It hydrates your skin and act as a primer too.
2. Followed up by @maccosmetics studio moisture cream. It is very important to moisturise your skin. For the people who think moisturiser makes your skin oily, you’re wrong here - moisturiser hydrates your skin. So do use a moisturiser before you apply makeup.
3. @maccosmetics strobe cream - just to add some shine.
4. Using @maccosmetics face and body foundation. It is very important to choose your foundation shade right. Using a buffing brush (also known as stippling brush) to blend. This foundation is for medium coverage- hence not very tough on blending. I use this one for daily purpose. It has moisturiser in it- so not very heavy too.
5. Using @maccosmetics studio conceal and correct Duo to hide my under eyes. You can avoid this step if you feel your under eyes are not too dark.
6. Using @maccosmetics studio finish concealer and blending it with a blending brush. You may also use a beauty blender.
7. Applying @lauramercier translucent powder with the same blending brush under the eyes- to fix the concealer and base and also because I tend to get creases due to my dry skin.
8. Shape and fill your brows. I am using @benefitcosmetics Brow Zing palatte.
9. Using @kikomilanoindia face palatte. It is amazing and comes with bronzer, blusher and highlighter. Applying bronzer-just to add some warmness to your face. Then applying blusher. 
10. Give your eyes a feline flick with winged eyeliner. I am using @clinique gel eyeliner - it is so smooth to apply.
11. Applying @benefitcosmetics bad gal mascara.
12. Last but not the least- adding a tint of pink to my lips. Used @maccosmetics velvet teddy lipshade.

Hope you guys enjoyed the video!! Let me know what would you want to see next!! #bhavykala #makeuptutorial #makeupbybhavykala #makeup #makeupartist #mua

Featuring: My stunning bride Anushka ✨

Textured skin is real, beautiful, and absolutely normal — but it does need a slightly different approach when it comes to makeup. Here’s what I keep in mind to ensure the skin looks smooth, radiant, and fresh — without masking its natural beauty:

✅ Do: Focus on skin prep

Think hydration, not heavy primers. Prepping the skin with a lightweight, non-greasy moisturizer and a smoothing primer helps blur texture without layering on too much.
Even Icing the skin before makeup helps tighten pores, control oil, and give a fresh, smooth base.

❌ Don’t: Layer on too much base

The more product you pile on, the more visible the texture becomes.
Heavy foundations and powders settle into pores and fine lines. Less is more — a thin, buildable base gives a smoother, more skin-like finish.

✅ Do: Use highlighter carefully

If the cheekbones are textured, avoid strong powder highlights that can catch and reflect unevenly.
Instead, use a cream highlighter only where the texture is minimal — and blend it gently with a damp beauty blender for a seamless glow.

❌ Don’t: Apply chunky glitter or intense shimmer

Shimmery products can amplify texture. Opt for soft, diffused finishes instead of anything frosty or sparkly.

✅ Do: Shift focus to other features

For Anushka, we kept the skin fresh and focused attention on her eyes and lips.
This creates visual balance and draws attention away from texture without hiding it.

❌ Don’t: Try to ‘erase’ texture

Let’s be honest — we’re makeup artists, not plastic surgeons.
Texture can’t be removed, but it can be minimized with proper prep and thoughtful techniques. The goal is not to hide, but to avoid exaggerating it with heavy, cakey looks.

Real skin is beautiful skin. With the right approach, even textured skin can look soft, smooth, and stunning — just like Anushka.

latestPosts.caption:
The nature of work like ours needs full commitment.

It was 25th November 2024. I had just packed up from Jim Corbett that morning, glammed a bride in the afternoon on my way, and then reached Shivangi’s venue in the evening.

Never in my 6 years of experience had I felt as unwell as I did on that drive. I remember quietly chanting my daily prayer, just asking for strength.

And somehow, the moment I saw Shivangi, everything shifted. She looked so graceful, so serene — and I was reminded exactly why I do what I do.

Grateful beyond words for the trust my brides place in me.
Wedding season can be intense, but the love and grace of brides like her make every single mile worth it. ✨
.
